==English==

===Etymology===
Latin ''[[acescens]]'', ''[[acescentis]]'', present participle of ''[[acescere]]'' to turn sour; [[inchoative]] of ''[[acere]]'' to be sour: compare French ''[[acescent]]''. See [[acid]]

===Pronunciation===
'''ace*scent'''
EIS-ent

===Adjective===
'''acescent'''

# Turning sour; readily becoming tart or acid; slightly sour - [[Faraday]]

====Translations====
*'''French''': ascescent

===Noun===
'''acescent'''

# A substance liable to become sour.

